# SonarCloud Standards

Follow these rules to keep SonarCloud warnings at zero.

## Node imports (S7772)

Use the `node:` protocol prefix for Node.js built-in modules:

```typescript
// Bad
import { readFileSync } from 'fs';
import { resolve } from 'path';

// Good
import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';
import { resolve } from 'node:path';
```

Applies to: `fs`, `path`, `url`, `readline`, `crypto`, `os`, `child_process`, `stream`, `util`, `events`

## Read-only props (S6759)

Always wrap React component props with `Readonly<>`:

```typescript
// Bad
function MyComponent({ name, onClick }: { name: string; onClick: () => void }) {}

// Good
function MyComponent({ name, onClick }: Readonly<{ name: string; onClick: () => void }>) {}
```

## Number globals (S7773)

Use `Number.parseInt` and `Number.parseFloat` instead of bare globals:

```typescript
// Bad
parseInt(value, 10);
parseFloat(value);

// Good
Number.parseInt(value, 10);
Number.parseFloat(value);
```

## No nested ternaries (S3358)

Extract nested ternary operations into variables or helper functions:

```typescript
// Bad
const color = active ? (hovered ? 'green' : 'blue') : 'gray';

// Good
const activeColor = hovered ? 'green' : 'blue';
const color = active ? activeColor : 'gray';
```

## No array index keys (S6479)

Use unique identifiers for React `key` props, not array indices:

```typescript
// Bad
items.map((item, i) => <li key={i}>{item.name}</li>)

// Good
items.map((item) => <li key={item.id}>{item.name}</li>)
```

## No zero fractions (S7748)

Don't use `.0` on whole numbers:

```typescript
// Bad
const opacity = 1.0;

// Good
const opacity = 1;
```

## Use globalThis (S7764)

Prefer `globalThis` over `window`:

```typescript
// Bad
window.addEventListener('resize', handler);

// Good
globalThis.addEventListener('resize', handler);
```

## Use new Array() (S7723)

```typescript
// Bad
Array(5).fill(null)

// Good
new Array(5).fill(null)
```

## Batch array pushes (S7778)

```typescript
// Bad
arr.push(a);
arr.push(b);
arr.push(c);

// Good
arr.push(a, b, c);
```

## Cognitive complexity (S3776)

Keep function complexity at or below 15. Extract helper functions to reduce nesting.

## Accessibility (S1082, S6848, S6853)

- Clickable `<div>` elements need `role="button"`, `tabIndex={0}`, and `onKeyDown`
- Form `<label>` elements must have a matching `htmlFor` attribute

## Redundant fragments (S6749)

Don't wrap a single child in `<>...</>`.

## React Three Fiber (S6747)

R3F props like `position`, `rotation`, `args`, `castShadow`, `intensity`, `roughness`, `metalness`, `emissive` are valid — SonarLint flags them as false positives. These warnings are suppressed at the project level.
